agentID.description: The agent's unique identification number. Each location will have a unique number assigned by MoneyGram.

agentSequence.description: The unique POS number that identifies an individual POS at the agent location. Other locations may have POS devices with the same number. The number is provided by MoneyGram and should not be hard-coded by the agent.

language.description: The language in which errors and other language-specific information is returned. en is English (default); de is German; es is Spanish; fr is French

timeStamp.description: The date and time the request was sent. Format: CCYY-MM- DDThh:mm:ss.sss-hh:mm

apiVersion.description: The API version the agent application uses.

clientSoftwareVersion.description: The version of the agent application being used. This value is set by the agent and can be used for debugging purposes. MoneyGram stores this information in its systems, but does not check or return the value. It is used when an agent places a technical call to verify problems between different versions.

productVariant.description: Field does not apply to this product

operatorName.description: If data is included, it must be information from the agent's system. If data is included, it must not be editable by the user of the agent application. If data is not included, the agent must provide it to MoneyGram upon request in the event of an audit or other investigation

amountIncludingFee.description: Data is required in one and onlyone of the following: amountIncludingFee, amountExcludingFee, receiveAmount. The GUI must provide input for at least one of the following: amountIncludingFee, amountExcludingFee, receiveAmount

amountExcludingFee.description: Data is required in one and onlyone of the following: amountIncludingFee, amountExcludingFee, receiveAmount. The GUI must provide input for at least one of the following: amountIncludingFee, amountExcludingFee, receiveAmount

receiveAmount.description: Data is required in one and only one of the following: amountIncludingFee, amountExcludingFee, receiveAmount. The GUI must provide input for at least one of the following: amountIncludingFee, amountExcludingFee, receiveAmount. Field cannot be used to determine fees to countries with indicative rates.

receiveCountry.description: The country in which the transaction is to be received.

deliveryOption.description: If a value is provided and allOptions is true,the feeLookupResponse returns results for the specified delivery option in all available receive currencies. If no value is provided and allOptions is false,the value defaults to WILL_CALL

mgiRewardsNumber.description: The sender's MoneyGram Rewards number. If provided,transaction fee may include a loyalty discount

receiveCode.description: Field does not apply to this product

receiveCurrency.description: Must be a valid currency code. If allOptions is true and deliveryOption is provided, the value of receiveCurrency is ignored. If allOptions is false, the feeLookupResponse returns a result for the specified delivery option (or WILL_CALL if none is specified) and receive currency

sendCurrency.description: Must be a valid currency code. If a value is provided, thefeeLookupResponse returns only delivery options using the specified send currency

mgCustomerReceiveNumber.description: The unique MoneyGram-managed RRN (receiver registration number) that identifies the receiver of the transaction. If a value is provided,the feeLookupResponse returns only the delivery option for the specified RRN

defaultInformationalFee.description: Field does not apply to this product

serviceOfferingID.description: Field does not apply to this product

defaultMaxFee.description: Field does not apply to this product

allOptions.description: If true, the feeLookupResponse returns results for all delivery options and receive currencies available to the agent. If false, the feeLookupResponse returns a single result for the specified deliveryOption and receiveCurrency

promoCode.description: The promotional code to apply to the transaction.

receiveCountry.description: Must be a valid country code. Use value of receiveCountry returned by feeLookupResponse for selected delivery option.

deliveryOption.description: Must be a valid delivery option. Use value of deliveryOption returned by feeLookupResponse for selected delivery option

thirdPartyType.description: Valid values: NONE, ORG, PERSON. If the transaction is being sent on behalf of someone other than the sender, whether it is being sent for a person or an organization. If the amount is above the agent's third party profile limit and the agent application allows third-party transactions, the agent must ask whether the transaction is on behalf of a third party. If the agent application allows third-party transactions, a field to select the type of third-party transaction must be provided on the GUI. If the agent application does not allow third-party transactions, the agent must communicate this to an account representative

receiveAgentID.description: Use value of receiveAgentID returned by feeLookupResponse for selected delivery option. Data is required if receiveAgentID is returned in the feeInformation section of the feeLookupResponse for the selected delivery option

customerReceiveNumber.description: Use value provided by consumer or returned in queryRegistrationByNamesResponse. If it is a directed send transaction, prompt for the customerReceiverNumber.

cardSwiped.description: Field does not apply to this product

amount.description: Use value of sendAmount from feeLookupResponse.
